
<div class="pure-g">
  <div class="pure-u-2-3">
  
    <p>Who do you share with and why?</p>

    <p>
      Besides our staff, we share this info with 
      {{input type="text" value=model.statement.thirdPartySharing placeholder="3rd party"}},
      and 
      {{input type="text" value=model.statement.thirdPartySharingMore placeholder="3rd party"}}
      in order to 
      {{input type="text" value=model.statement.thirdPartySharingWhy placeholder="take action connected to the purpose for collection"}}.
    </p>

    {{#each party in model.statement.sharingParties}}
      <div>
        <p>
          We also share this info with 
          {{input type="text" placeholder="3rd party"}},
          and 
          {{input type="text" placeholder="3rd party"}}
          in order to 
          {{input type="text" placeholder="take action connected to the purpose for collection"}}.
        </p>
      </div>
    {{/each}}

    <p>  
      <button {{action "addParty"}} class="pure-button pure-button-secondary">we have another reason</button>  
    </p>

  </div>

  <div class="pure-u-1-3">
    <button type="button">Is that a problem?</button>

    <div>
      <p>
        You need to have a valid reason to share information with outside parties, related to your purpose for collecting it. This doesn’t apply if you gathered the information from a public source, or you have asked the user’s permissions.
      </p>

      <p>
        See <a href="https://privacy.org.nz/limits-on-use-of-personal-information-principle-ten/">Privacy Principle 10</a>, 
        and <a href="https://privacy.org.nz/limits-on-disclosure-of-personal-information-principle-eleven/#collection">Privacy Principle 11</a> 
        for more.
      </p>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>
